  <a href="#1" id="1">
   President Mikhail S. Gorbachev said today that thousands of striking coal miners and other workers are urging railway employees to join the work stoppage and that the unrest threatens his economic reforms.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The miners are demanding more local control over their industry as well as higher wages and better living conditions.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Miners in the Donetsk Basin are demanding a 40 percent wage increase for night work, improved living conditions, a fixed day off and retirement after 20 years of underground work.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   The strikes are believed to be the nation's worst since the 1920s, when the country was gripped in revolution, civil war and a power struggle.
  </a>
